hopobject.body: When do you want me to start? orderfioricetcod.com Coumou, along with Alexander Robinson of the Universidad Complutense de Madrid, used a computerized climate model to predict how many extreme heat waves will occur over the next few decades. Dubbed "3-sigma" events, these heat waves have unusually high temperatures that are three standard deviations from the historical average, and are expected to become the norm over the course of the 21st century.
